# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#  THE scene COMMAND
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

#  Basic use:
#    scene background_name

#  With a transition:
#    scene background_name with transition_name

#  Example:
#    scene classroom
#    scene hallway with dissolve
#    scene park_day with fade


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#  FILE NAMING RULES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

#  Your image file:    game/images/rainy_street.png
#  Your scene command: scene rainy_street
#
#  Rules:
#    - Use lowercase letters
#    - Use underscores instead of spaces  (park_day, not "park day")
#    - No special characters (!@#$%...)
#    - The name in the command must EXACTLY match the filename


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#  TRANSITIONS — Choose the feeling
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

#  with dissolve   →  smooth blend, soft, gentle
#                     USE FOR: calm scene changes, slow mood shifts

#  with fade       →  goes to black, then reveals new scene
#                     USE FOR: time passing, dramatic moments, endings

#  with pixellate  →  glitchy digital break-up effect
#                     USE FOR: dream sequences, flashbacks, tech themes

#  with move       →  new scene slides in from the side
#                     USE FOR: physical movement, location change

#  (no transition) →  instant cut, jarring and abrupt
#                     USE FOR: shock, sudden jumps, action moments


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#  COLOR → MOOD QUICK GUIDE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

#  BLUES & COOL GRAYS  →  calm, sad, lonely, ordinary, thoughtful
#  BRIGHT GREENS       →  hopeful, free, natural, growing, alive
#  WARM YELLOWS/CREAM  →  comfortable, social, nostalgic, safe
#  DEEP NAVY/DARK BLUE →  mysterious, lonely, nighttime, unknown
#  DARK GRAY/CHARCOAL  →  tense, threatening, heavy, stuck
#  WARM BROWNS         →  cozy, focused, thoughtful, hiding away
#  PURPLES             →  magical, dreamy, strange, fantastical
#  REDS/PINKS          →  love, excitement, danger, urgency


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#  COMMON MISTAKES TO AVOID
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

#  ❌  scene Classroom        (capital letters cause errors)
#  ✅  scene classroom

#  ❌  scene park day         (spaces in name cause errors)
#  ✅  scene park_day

#  ❌  scene bedroom.png      (don't include the file extension)
#  ✅  scene bedroom

#  ❌  scene with dissolve    (forgot the background name!)
#  ✅  scene hallway with dissolve


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#  THINKING LIKE A VISUAL STORYTELLER
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

#  Ask yourself these questions when choosing a background:
#
#  1. How do I want the PLAYER to feel right now?
#  2. Does the background MATCH the dialogue — or contradict it on purpose?
#  3. Does the TRANSITION reflect the mood of the scene change?
#  4. What time of day / weather / location fits this moment?
#  5. Would a different color version of the same background change the feeling?
